abstract: >-
  Synapse is a portable, file-based academic knowledge base for management and
  business sustainability research. Each peer-reviewed article becomes one
  Markdown note with YAML frontmatter (trusted bibliographic metadata, a
  controlled-vocabulary topic taxonomy, and three custom analytic fields:
  unit_of_analysis, level_of_theory, dependent_variable_family) and a
  human-readable distillation (research question, mechanism, theoretical
  contribution, limitations, future research, APA citation). A small Python
  pipeline derives a SQLite index, a CSV export, and a BibTeX file from the
  notes, while a verbatim-abstract validator anchors trust in the source PDF.
  This release contains 62 curated notes from the Network for Business
  Sustainability (NBS) February 2026 monthly digest.
